safenet.jhsm

Class Md

  • java.lang.Object
    • safenet.jhsm.Md

  • public class Md
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the static interface to Safenet implementation of Java HSM interface.

    This Java interface utilizes Java Native Interface (JNI) to communicate with the HSM. As such, it is operating system specific.

    The interface is only useful for accessing custom API FMs from Java, without writing JNI wrappers to access the C API of the FM.

    • Method Detail

      • MD_Initialize

        public static MD_RV MD_Initialize(java.lang.Object pReserved)

        Initialize the message dispatch library. The message dispatch library is designed to operate on a stable HSM system (either local or remote to the Host computer). During the initialization of the message dispatch library, the number of accessible HSMs is determined and HSM indices are allocated to accessible HSMs. These variables are utilized in other functions; therefore, if the HSM system should change the message dispatch library should be re-initialized.

        Until this function is called, all other functions will return MDR_NOT_INITIALIZED

        Returns:
        The status of operation

      • MD_Finalize

        public static void MD_Finalize(java.lang.Object pReserved)

        Finalize the message dispatch library.

        After this function returns, only the MD_Initialize function can be called. All other functions will return MDR_NOT_INITIALIZED error code.

      • MD_GetHsmCount

        public static MD_RV MD_GetHsmCount(int[] pHsmCount)
        Retrieve the number of visible HSM(s). Note that this function retrieves the number of accessible HSMs at the time the message dispatch library was initialized (i.e. the time the MD_Initialize () function was called)
        Parameters:
        pHsmCount - Integer array for method to return HSM count. This parameter MUST NOT be null. First element of array pHsmCount will be modified to hold output value and array size is always 1.
        Returns:
        The status of operation

      • MD_GetHsmState

        public static MD_RV MD_GetHsmState(int hsmIndex,
                                   HSM_STATE[] pState,
                                   int[] pErrorCode)
        Retrieve the state for a specified HSM.
        Parameters:
        hsmIndex - Zero based index of the HSM to query. For remote HSMs, HSMs are numbered according to the order that the HSMs IP addresses were entered in the ET_HSM_NETCLIENT_SERVERLIST registry key.
        pState - Address of a variable to hold the result. This parameter MUST NOT be null. First element of array pState will be modified to hold output value and array size is always 1.
        pErrorCode - Error code to report unexpected failure in HSM. This parameter MAY BE assigned null. First element of array pErrorCode will be modified to hold output value and array size is always 1.
        Returns:
        The status of operation.

      • MD_SendReceive

        public static MD_RV MD_SendReceive(int hsmIndex,
                                   int originatorId,
                                   short fmNumber,
                                   Md_Buffer[] pReq,
                                   int reserve,
                                   Md_Buffer[] pResp,
                                   int[] pReceivedLen,
                                   int[] pFmStatus)
        Send a request a specific HSM and resceive a response. MD_SendReceive function is is very specific about the pReq and pResp buffer. When user construct this buffer, it is compulsory to instantiate the last buffer as a zero length buffer. An example is provided. 
         Md_Buffer[] pReq  = new Md_Buffer[2];  
 Md_Buffer[] pResp = new Md_Buffer[2];
 
 pReq[0] = new Md_Buffer(user_byte_buffer);
 pReq[1] = new Md_Buffer(0);    // Terminate buffer

 pResp[0] = new Md_Buffer(expected_return_length);
 pResp[1] = new Md_Buffer(0);   // Terminate buffer
        Parameters:
        hsmIndex - Zero based index of the HSM to query. For remote HSMs, HSMs are numbered according to the order that the HSMs IP addresses were entered in the ET_HSM_NETCLIENT_SERVERLIST registry key.
        originatorId - Id of the request originator. This Id is typically.0, only if the calling application is acting as a proxy this would be non-zero.
        fmNumber - Identifier of the Functionality Module to send the request to. For User FMs this should be 0x100.
        pReq - Send buffer. The final element in the array MUST BE null terminated.
        reserve - Reserved for future use. Currently must be set to zero
        pResp - Receive buffer. The final element in the array MUST BE null terminated.
        pReceivedLen - Number of valid entries in receive buffer pResp. The value of this parameter MAY BE assigned null . First element of array pReceivedLen will be modified to hold output value. and array size is always 1.
        pFmStatus - Retuns FM internal status code. The value of theis parameter MAY BE assigned null. First element of array pFmStatus will be modified to hold output value and array size is always 1.
        Returns:
        The status of operation
        See Also:
        MDR

      • MD_GetParameter

        public static MD_RV MD_GetParameter(MD_PARAMETER parameter,
                                    java.lang.Object[] pValue)
        Obtain the value of a HSM parameter.

        The pValue parameter only accepts object arrays of Integer for this version of API.

        Note that unlike it's C counter part, this interface only requires 2 parameters. Java is able to recognize the type of object that is passed in to the function, as such there is no need to include the size of pValue. An example to use this parameter is provided : 

         
  Integer[] paramValue  = new Integer[1];
  Md.MD_GetParameter(MDP.MAX_BUFFER_LENGTH, paramValue);
  System.out.println(paramValue[0].longValue());
        Parameters:
        parameter - The parameter whose value is being queried
        pValue - Object array to hold return value. First element of array pValue will be modified to hold output value and array size is always 1.
        Returns:
        The status of operation
        See Also:
        MDR
